Each element in result must be UNIQUE
Even if a number appears many times → take it only once
📌 Example
nums1 = [1,2,2,1]
nums2 = [2,2]

👉 Common element = 2
👉 But we only take it once

✅ Output: [2]

Solution : 
fun main() {
 val nums1 = intArrayOf(1,2,2,1)
 val nums2 = intArrayOf(2,2)
 
    val set = mutableSetOf<Int>()
    val result = mutableSetOf<Int>()
    
    for(i in nums1){
        set.add(i)
    }
    
    for(i in nums2){
        if(set.contains(i)){
            result.add(i)
     
        }
    }
    print(result)
}
